From Bernward Averwald Subject Re xdm and env vars In article AA sun MIL writes Hi, I am using xdm on X R with OW and Xview on Sun s and SPARCs running SunOS Prior to using xdm, I used to set PATH and other environment variables like MANPATH, HELPPATH, ARCH, etc in my login file With xdm, the login file doesn't get executed and therefore neither the olwm root window nor my applications know about these variables I always use the following in my t cshrc f LOGIN then source home login endif and in login setenv LOGIN So I don't need to set all environment variables in my cshrc, but they get set if I login via xdm or xon xrsh rx and so on Hope this helps, Bernward Bernward Averwald, Heinrichstr , D Dortmund , Voice FAX , e mail I think I need a Lear Jet